 and branding style guide for Maker’s Row to ensure a high-quality, consistent experience across all platforms. </li> <li>Collaborate with a cross discipline team to create and execute experience style guides, interaction patterns, and information design standards</li> <li>Provide leadership to the product team and foster a culture of innovation, excellence and accountability</li> <li>Be an evangelist for UX and UI best practices and design excellence across the products/projects being designed</li> <li>Track and optimize productivity through monitoring KPIs and integral data points</li> <li>Direct and manage user research initiatives whilst continually listening to users insights </li> <li>Regularly interpret KPI-based data and analytics to provide insights, recommendations and optimizations and reassess the product direction</li> <br /><br /></ul><strong>Requirements<br /></strong><ul> <li>At least 3 years of product leadership</li> <li>at least 5 years of UX/UI Experience</li> <li>Graphic Design, Digital Media Design or Communication Design degree and minimum 4+ years of work experience (startup/ ecommerce experience a bonus)</li> <li>Exceptional portfolio with a focus on creative UX/UI solution and solid information architecture for desktop and mobile experiences</li> <li>Proven ability to think outside the box, and create delightful, simple, and beautiful user experiences</li> <li>Knowledge of HTML, CSS and responsive design techniques</li> <li>Strong understanding of design - typography, composition and color theory</li> <li>Responsible self-starter, innovative thinker, analytic, detail oriented; comfortable in a results-drive business environment</li> <li>Highly proficient in Adobe Creative Suite (Photoshop, Illustrator a must) with a knowledge of Google Analytics, MailChimp (bonus) or similar, Wordpress, Google Docs and Shopify (bonus) or similar.</li> <br /><br /></ul><strong>Benefits<br /></strong><ul> <li> <strong>Prime Location: </strong>We are based in 